title: Two men found dead at home in Sydney’s northwest
description: Two men have been found dead at a property in Sydney's northwest.  Emergency services were called to the home in Glenorie just after 8.30 am on Saturday morning.   The men, both aged 28, were found with laceration injuries and pronounced dead at the scene.

title: US warship docked in Israel sparks heightened Middle East tensions
description: A US destroyer is docked in Israel near its border with Egypt, with Israeli media claiming the ship's arrival was preplanned as part of ongoing cooperation between the two nations.  Iranian Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi has acknowledged the show of force, saying, “Iran’s missiles will never be the subject of any negotiations.”  “I will repeat it again, the Islamic Republic of Iran … is also ready for war.”

title: Public hospitals receive $25 billion in additional funding
description: Australian Medical Association President Dr Danielle McMullen says the new funding deal for public hospitals has given them “certainty”.  The Australian government will provide $25 billion in additional funding for public hospitals over the next five years.

title: More work is needed to ‘improve’ the functionality of public hospitals
description: Australian Medical Association President Dr Danielle McMullen says more work needs to be done to “improve” the functionality of public hospitals.

title: Rising inflation is what Jim Chalmers ‘was looking for’
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond says the rising inflation is what Treasurer Jim Chalmers “was looking for”.

title: Albanese government ‘very happy’ to let bracket creep continue
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond says the Albanese government’s budget will receive higher revenue as a result of bracket creep.  Mr Bond said it seems the Albanese government is “very happy” to let bracket creep go on and make Australians pay more tax, without giving us anything back”.

title: Inflation is the ‘most insidious tax’ of all
description: Eminence Advisory Dimitri Burshtein says inflation is the “most insidious tax” of all.  Mr Burshtein told Sky News host Caleb Bond that it’s a tax people pay for a “bad government”.

title: Labor’s ‘economic irresponsibility’ amplifies the cost-of-living crisis
description: Eminence Advisory Dimitri Burshtein calls out Labor’s “economic irresponsibility” and the cost-of-living crisis Australians face.

title: Middle-income earners will get ‘hit the worst’ under Albanese’s tax policies
description: Eminence Advisory Dimitri Burshtein says middle-income earners will get “hit the worst” by the Albanese government’s tax policies.

title: Andrew Hastie can ‘afford to wait’ for Liberal leadership
description: Sky News contributor Joe Hildebrand says Andrew Hastie can “afford to wait” for the leadership position within the Liberal Party.

title: Angus Taylor’s only ‘chance’ at Liberal leadership is now
description: Sky News contributor Joe Hildebrand says if Angus Taylor doesn’t contest the Liberal leadership, he will “never have a chance” again.

title: Andrew Hastie is not ‘ready’ for the Liberal Party leadership
description: GT Communications Gemma Tognini says Andrew Hastie is not “ready” for the Liberal Party leadership position.

title: Union memberships have been ‘falling exponentially’
description: GT Communications Gemma Tognini says union memberships have been “falling exponentially” for many years.

title: Backlash from businesses after unions may be granted digital work systems
description: Sky News contributor Jaimee Rogers says there are “concerns” from businesses about unions potentially being granted access to any company's digital work systems.

title: Unions accessing businesses AI systems is a ‘disaster waiting to happen’
description: Sky News contributor Jaimee Rogers says unions potentially accessing businesses' AI systems is a “disaster waiting to happen”.
